sentences: Anja Ignatius (July 2, 1911 – April 10, 1995) was a Finnish violinist and music educator, mainly known as a chamber musician.
She performed with the Helsinki Philharmonic Orchestra in 1928.
Between 1929 and 1931, she studied with Carl Flesch in Berlin.
From 1953 to 1961, she played first violin with the Helsinki Quartet; from 1961 to 1965, she performed in a trio with France Ellegaard and Pentti Rautawaara.
